Add runnable example scenarios under `examples/`: six self-contained scripts that build a throwaway git corpus and run real `decree` commands (`why`, `intent-check`, `intent-review`, `health`, and the `--under` governs-gap), each printing real output with a `VALUE:` line (what you gain) and a `HONESTY:` line (where decree refuses to overclaim — advisory vs finding, structural vs semantic, convention vs certainty). They walk the lifecycle of one change (before → while → after → over time), use pinned IDs for reproducibility, and double as smoke tests for the `--json` shapes and the exit-code contract.
